Torres made his debut for the senior team on 6 September 2003 in a [[exhibition_game|friendly]] against [[Portugal_national_football_team|Portugal]].<ref name="Torres"/> His first goal for Spain came against [[Italy_national_football_team|Italy]] on 28 April 2004.<ref name="Torres"/> He was selected for the Spanish squad for [[UEFA_Euro_2004|UEFA Euro 2004]].<ref name="Torres"/> After appearing as a late substitute in Spain's first two group games, he started for the deciding game against Portugal.<ref name="Torres"/> Spain were losing 1–0 and, towards the end of the game, he hit the post.<ref name="Torres"/>
